Exercise 1: Eulerian graph

library("Biostrings")
library("Rgraphviz")
library("biomaRt")

# scan file with datatype=character, convert to DNAStringSet
reads = DNAStringSet(scan("SequencingReads.txt", character()))
numreads = length(reads)

# subset reads: first 4 nucleotides, then last 4 (as first 4 of the reversed read...)
readB = as.character(subseq(reads, 1, 4))
readE = as.character(reverse(subseq(reverse(reads), 1, 4)))

# nodes list is every different 4-mer found above
nodes = sort(unique(c(readB, readE)))
numnodes = length(nodes)
edgelabels = 1:numreads
names(edgelabels) = paste(readB, readE, sep='~')

A = matrix(0, nrow=numnodes, ncol=numnodes, dimnames=list(nodes, nodes))
# loop through read list and increment the corresponding element in A
#   (identified by the start and end 4-mers)
for (n in 1:numreads) {
    nfrom = readB[n]
    nto = readE[n]
    A[nfrom, nto] = A[nfrom, nto]+1
}

grEuler = graphAM(adjMat=A, values=list(weight=1), edgemode="directed")
edgeattr = list(label=edgelabels)

grattr = getDefaultAttrs()
grattr$node$width = 3.5
grattr$node$height = 1.5
grattr$node$fontsize = 16
grattr$node$shape = "ellipse"
grattr$edge$arrowsize = 1
grattr$edge$minlen = 3
grattr$edge$fontsize = 18
grattr$edge$labelfontsize = 18

plot(grEuler, edgeAttrs=edgeattr, attrs=grattr)

Eulerian path and contig

# this is (visually) the order edges are visted in a path through the graph
edgepath = c(22, 6, 9, 10, 18, 5, 15, 13, 12, 3, 19, 14, 2, 21, 17, 11, 4, 1, 7, 20, 16, 8)

# concatenate reads in the order of the path,
# after removing the left overlap (but keep it for the first one)
contig = DNAStringSet(paste(c(subseq(reads[edgepath[1]], 1, 4), subseq(reads[edgepath], 5)), collapse=''))
names(contig) = "Week2Contig"

# save as Fasta file
writeXStringSet(contig, "Week2Contig.fa")

  • Create a barplot of the sliding window base frequencies.
base.freqs = letterFrequencyInSlidingView(contig[[1]], 20, DNA_BASES, as.prob=T)

# cosmetic aspects of the plot with par()
par(las=1, bg="white")
# need to transpose the matrix to get frequencies vertically
barplot(t(base.freqs), col=2:5, border='NA')
# add a legend to show which color is which base
legend("top", DNA_BASES, col=2:5, pch=15, cex=.8, horiz=T)
axis(1)

Exercise 2: Align your contig to the Chicken genome

  1. Start from the result of Exercise 1: load the assembled contig as a DNAString
  2. Download the transcript found at chr21:295510-295980 on the Chicken genome using biomaRt and keep only the part between nucleotides 335 and 806
  3. Align these two sequences using a match score of +1, mismatch score of -1 and gap penalty of -2 (you need to define the missing variables here: see scoring matrices)
ensembl = useMart("ensembl", "ggallus_gene_ensembl")
ensembl_qry = getSequence(chromosome=21, start=295510, end=295980, type=c("uniprot_gn_symbol","start_position","strand"), seqType="cdna", mart=ensembl)
gg_seq = subseq(DNAString(ensembl_qry$cdna), 335, 806)

qry_seq = readDNAStringSet("Week2Contig.fa")[[1]]

scMatrix = nucleotideSubstitutionMatrix(match=1, mismatch=-1, baseOnly=TRUE)
gapPenalty = -2
pairwiseAlignment(qry_seq, gg_seq, substitutionMatrix=scMatrix, gapOpening=0, gapExtension=gapPenalty)
